column3: The caustic Adder. Damage from its poison bite is always lethal.
The dauntless Bloodhound. It leaps to oppose new creatures when they are played.
The watchful Bullfrog. It leaps in the way of attacking flyers.
The undying Cat. Sacrificing the poor beast does not kill it.
The flighty Elk. It moves after attacking.
The nascent Fawn. It quickly grows into an Elk.
Hm. The licentious Field Mice. You will draw a copy when they are played.
The monstrous Grizzly. Its form speaks enough of its efficacy.
The holy Mantis God. A perfect incarnation of terror.
The omnipresent Mole. It burrows and emerges to block any landborn attacker.
The stalwart Mole Man. The ultimate defense.
The conniving Raven. A blight upon the skies.
This level of brutish strength needs no explanation...
The bountiful Warren. It spawns a rabbit when it is played.
The young Wolf Cub. It grows into a Wolf after a single turn.
